        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1997459391" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13572969094545996271">Powerfully written, suspenseful book! I love books that are two stories in one—this one had the WWII story of Dorothy and Vivien and Jimmy and Henry, and then the story of Dorothy&apos;s daughter Lauren trying to solve the mystery of her mother&apos;s life.<br/><br/>The story starts with a bang! Set at a family party, where a strange man shows up and Lauren&apos;s loving, kind, wonderful mother Dorothy immediately stabs him to death.<br/><br/>When Dorothy is on her deathbed, she starts to ramble and become upset about something s</span>
  <span id="freeText13572969094545996271" style="display:none">Powerfully written, suspenseful book! I love books that are two stories in one—this one had the WWII story of Dorothy and Vivien and Jimmy and Henry, and then the story of Dorothy's daughter Lauren trying to solve the mystery of her mother's life.<br /><br />The story starts with a bang! Set at a family party, where a strange man shows up and Lauren's loving, kind, wonderful mother Dorothy immediately stabs him to death.<br /><br />When Dorothy is on her deathbed, she starts to ramble and become upset about something she did in the past, so Lauren becomes determined to figure out just what happened in her mother's life that led to that fatal party, to put her mother at peace.<br /><br />As the book alternates between Dorothy and Vivien and Jimmy during WWII, and Lauren's detective work, the clues build up. But every time I thought I had figured out what had happened, there would be a twist. Beautifully written, literary sort of thriller, this book should appeal to anyone who likes thrillers, historical fiction, or just any well-written fiction. I'm working my way through everything that this author has written and enjoying the books immensely!!</span>
  <a data-text-id="13572969094545996271" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


