    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_507873958" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/507873958" />
    <a title="Heidi " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/416888-heidi"><img alt="Heidi " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1206230156p2/416888.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/507873958?book_show_action=true">Jan 15, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Heidi " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Heidi " href="/user/show/416888-heidi">Heidi </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/416888-heidi?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/416888-heidi?shelf=2014-goal">2014-goal</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer507873958" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6038106133257450266">A friend once noted that I&apos;m a little miserly with my five-star ratings, and she&apos;s right. I have a lot of three- and four-star books on my list-- all really great reads-- but a book has to really hit me just right to earn that fifth star. The Secret Keeper was one of those books for me.<br/><br/>The sins of yesterday impacting the lives of today- check. <br/><br/>Characters (both major and minor) I&apos;d love to meet, lunch with or share a glass of wine with - check. <br/><br/>Filled with rich visual imagery from start to finish</span>
  <span id="freeText6038106133257450266" style="display:none">A friend once noted that I'm a little miserly with my five-star ratings, and she's right. I have a lot of three- and four-star books on my list-- all really great reads-- but a book has to really hit me just right to earn that fifth star. The Secret Keeper was one of those books for me.<br /><br />The sins of yesterday impacting the lives of today- check. <br /><br />Characters (both major and minor) I'd love to meet, lunch with or share a glass of wine with - check. <br /><br />Filled with rich visual imagery from start to finish - check. <br /><br />Thought about the book when I wasn't reading it - check. <br /><br />Continuously surprised me including its perfect "I didn't see that coming" ending - check.<br /><br />I'll leave others to write the kind of in-depth analysis so often seen on Goodreads. For me, this simply was my favorite kind of story - a five-star read!</span>
  <a data-text-id="6038106133257450266" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

